name: Wish You Were Here - 2014 Charity Calendar
description:
This is our third Annual Charity Calendar Project and this year we're donating 100% of the profits to Melbourne's Asylum Seeker Resource Centre. We hand picked a selection of incredible artists from all over the world and many different backgrounds to generously contribute to "Wish You Were Here" with a mind to illustrating their favourite city.  The calendar is a colourful vision of a rich and joyful world in which boarders are dissolved. 

Artworks include Cape Town by Studio Muti, Sydney by James Gulliver Hancock, Barcelona by Lydia Nichols, Delhi by Owen Gatley, Amsterdam by Lotta Nieminen, Montevideo by Martin Azambuja, Brighton by Ryan Gillett, Mykonos by Matt Chase, Copenhagen by Michelle Carlslund, Helsinki by Blanca GÃ³mez, New York by Nicholas Girling and Tokyo by Masako Kubo.

Size: 19cm x 30cm

Please note that as this item is a charity project, we are doing everything we can to maximise our donation to the Asylum Seeker Resource Centre. We have therefore chosen to charge $3 postage for our Australian customers. Thank you for your understanding.

name: Rubber Stamping Kit
description:
This clever little kit includes all the components necessary to make tw colour stamped images. These components include a green ink pad, a navy blue ink pad, 3 oversized stamps (that come in two parts) and a set square ruler to help align your two colours and achieve a perfect printed image every time. THe ink pads are made from non-toxic ink and the wood blocks from white maple that has been accredited by the Sustainable Forestry Initiative.

name: Greeting Card for Dads
description:
This card is a member of our Cards for a Cause range which means that  50% of the profits from this card will be donated to a charity and in this particular cards case, the charity is the Mirabel Foundation. 
The Mirabel Foundation assists Australia's children who have been orphaned or abandoned due to parental illicit drug use, restoring a childs sense of self-worth, belonging and hope for the future.
This card is Melbourne made and printed on FSC certified paper. The card is blank inside, comes with a quality, Melbourne made envelope and is packaged in an earth friendly, biodegradable sleeve.
